Detail of building of Peter Doelger's Brewery, showing statue, probably of Gambrinus, 56th Street, south side, between Sutton Place and First Avenue.

October 20, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

Sutton Place (formerly Avenue A), west side, south from E. 58th to 56th Streets. Prominently shown is a 14 story apartment house at the N. W. corner of this thoroughfare and E. 57th Street. A similar type structure was erected at the S. W. corner in the Spring of 1939. This site appears vacant in this photo.

Gift of Beecher Ogden

1937

Recreations & Hobbies: Quoit players pitching horse shoes at about East 56th Street and the East River. This is a Sutton Place locale, and possibly the players are residents of the apartment colony.
